\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 28. B. multinerve} DC., {\i Mém. Soc. Phys. Hist. Nat. Genève}{\b  4}: 500 (1828). Perennial c. 50 cm; stock rather stout, more or less densely covered with remains of dead leaves. Basal leaves linear-lanceolate, more or less distinctly petiolate; veins 7-11; upper cauline leaves linear-lanceolate to ovate from a cordate amplexicaul base, often long-acuminate; veins 11-45. Rays (5-)11-13(-20). Bracts 2-7, ovate, acute or acuminate; veins up to 21; bracteoles usually exceeding the flowers, ovate to suborbicular, apiculate, yellowish; veins 5-9(-13). Fruit 3·5-4 mm, dark brown; ridges narrowly winged.{\i  C. & S. Ural, and some outlying stations in C. Russia.} Rs (C, ?W). ({\i N. Asia.})
