\pard\f0\fs28  A very variable species which requires investigation before infraspecific taxa can be satisfactorily delimited. The two following are sufficiently distinct morphologically to merit recognition as subspecies at this stage, though more or less intermediate plants (e.g.{\i  B. parnassicum} Halácsy) occur in some parts of their range.
