  ({\b b}) Subsp. {\b cernuum} (Ten.) Arcangeli,{\i  Comp. Fl. Ital.} ed. 2, 590 (1894): Leaves linear, sessile; fruit c. 5 mm; ridges more or less winged.{\i  Pyrenees, S. Alps, Appennini, S. Carpathians, mountains of Balkan peninsula, S. Russia}.
