\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 30. B. elatum} Guss., {\i Fl. Sic. Prodr. }{\b 1}: 316 (1827). Perennial up to 150 cm; stock stout, woody, covered with remains of dead leaves. Basal leaves oblong-lanceolate to broadly lanceolate, somewhat narrowed to the amplexicaul base; veins 7-9; cauline leaves similar to the basal. Rays 6-14, slender, strict. Bracts (3-)5-7, lanceolate, acuminate; veins 5-7; bracteoles 5-6, much exceeding the flowers, linear-lanceolate, long-acuminate; veins 5(-7). Fruit c. 5 mm, oblong; ridges slender.{\i  Shady calcareous rocks. N. Sicilia} ({\i Madonie}). Si.
